on><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n Applies to:\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n Form widgets: <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"gge1665702634237.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gge1665702634237.html\" title=\"The utree widget enables users to view and navigate structured data as a hierarchy. Uniface provides a logical widget called Tree, which is mapped to utree.\">utree (Tree)</a>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n Activation:\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n Activated when the user double-clicks a tree or list item.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n Default behavior:\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n None\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n Behavior upon completion:\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n None\n </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"gaj1665703130372__topic_d83782e1_d83783e1_d83784e1_d83785e1_d83786e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d144655e131\">\n                       \n Parameters\n </h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"gaj1665703130372__li_d44780e1_d44781e1_d44782e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword parmname\">control</span>—input control used by the user; one of:\n <ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"gaj1665703130372__li_d44783e1_d44784e1_d44785e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">TREE</code>—user clicked in the\n                     tree view. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"gaj1665703130372__li_d44786e1_d44787e1_d44788e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">LIST</code>—user clicked in the\n                     list view.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"gaj1665703130372__li_d44789e1_d44790e1_d44791e1\"><span class=\"keyword parmname\">item</span>—value of the selected\n               tree node. </li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_7419788\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_7419788\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "trigger open Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 13, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 trigger open Interactive trigger that handles processing to open a tree node so that its subordinate items are shown in the list view of a Tree widget. Explain this code trigger open params string control : in ; TREE | LIST string item : in endparams ; <Your code here> end ; trigger open Copy Applies to: Form widgets: utree (Tree) Activation: Activated when the user double-clicks a tree or list item. Default behavior: None Behavior upon completion: None Parameters control —input control used by the user; one of: TREE —user clicked in the tree view. LIST —user clicked in the list view. item —value of the selected tree node. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}